This paper is primarily focused on natural language generation using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of variational autoencoders (VAEs) and variational encoder-decoders (VEDs), which are popular models in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores optimization heuristics and attention mechanisms, which are also relevant topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions experiments involving linear interpolation and sampling from a neighborhood, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV).
